(on loan from [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]) |clubnumber = |youthyears1 = 2007–2016 |youthclubs1 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] |years1 = 2016– |clubs1 = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] |caps1 = 0 |goals1 = 0 |years2 = 2017 |clubs2 = → [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] (loan) |caps2 = 15 |goals2 = 1 |years3 = 2017–2018 |clubs3 = → [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] (loan) |caps3 = 26 |goals3 = 0 |years4 = 2018– |clubs4 = → [[Sparta Rotterdam]] (loan) |caps4 = 1 |goals4 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2011 |nationalteam1 = [[England national under-16 football team|England U16]] |nationalcaps1 = 5 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2011 |nationalteam2 = [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] |nationalcaps2 = 5 |nationalgoals2 = 0 |nationalyears3 = 2014 |nationalteam3 = [[England national under-20 football team|England U20]] |nationalcaps3 = 1 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |club-update = 08:04, 20 September 2018 (UTC) |ntupdate = 17:46, 14 January 2017 (UTC) }} '''Sheik Mohamed Fankaty Dabo''' (born 11 October 1995) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Sparta Rotterdam]], on loan from [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. ==Club career== Dabo began his career with [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]. On 11 January 2017, along with Chelsea teammates [[Charlie Colkett]] and [[Islam Feruz]], Dabo joined League One side [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] on loan for the remainder of the 2016–17 season.{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/38589947|title=Charlie Colkett, Islam Feruz and Fankaty Dabo: Chelsea trio join Swindon on loan|date=11 January 2017|accessdate=12 January 2017|publisher=BBC Sport}} Three days later, Dabo made his Swindon Town debut in a 2–1 away victory against Bolton Wanderers, featuring for the entire 90 minutes. On 5 February 2017, Dabo scored his first goal for Swindon in their local derby against [[Oxford United F.C.|Oxford United]]. On 25 June 2017, Dabo joined Dutch side [[SBV Vitesse|Vitesse]] on a season-long loan.{{Cite news |title=Vitesse loan for defender Dabo |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2017/06/vitesse-loan-for-defender-dabo.html |publisher=Chelsea Official Site |date=25 June 2017 |accessdate=25 June 2017}} In August 2018 Dabo returned on loan to the Netherlands, this time with [[Sparta Rotterdam]].https://www.sparta-rotterdam.nl/fankaty-dabo-komt-chelsea/ ==International career== Dabo was born in England and is of Sierra Leonean descent.{{cite web|url=http://www.chelseafc.com/teams/on-loan-players/fankaty-dabo.html|title=Fankaty Dabo|website=www.chelseafc.com}} He has represented England at [[England national under-16 football team|under-16]], [[England national under-17 football team|under-17]] and [[England national under-20 football team|under-20]] youth levels.{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/england/all-teams/players/d/fankaty-dabo|title=Profile|accessdate=14 January 2017|publisher=The Football Association}} ==Career statistics== {{updated|match played 12 May
